      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BERRINGA PADDY (8) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by 1.75 lengths at this track in a handy 22.70 beating Pretty Panama. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from three attempts. One of the key runners again. BUB WHO (4) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing sixth (26.63) in a Grade 5 at Warragul. Solid record here at this trip including two wins. Likely to play a prominent role. SICILY (7) turned spotting a big start finishing fourth (23.15) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Some good form is emerging from his last run. Should be about the money. SQUEEGEE'S RIDE (2) collected a minor prize last start at big odds and must be considered.",
